results.p: Jan 25, 2024 — History of the national anthem. “O Canada” was proclaimed Canada's national anthem in 1980, a century after it was first sung in 1880.
Aug 12, 2024 — O Canada, national anthem of Canada. It was proclaimed the official national anthem on July 1, 1980. “God Save the Queen” remains the royal anthem of Canada.
"O Canada" (French: Ô Canada) is the national anthem of Canada. The song was originally commissioned by Lieutenant Governor of Quebec Théodore Robitaille.
